full_threads.body:
Hi Adrian,

Thanks so much for sending through the screenshot.

We did find her entry from May 28, 2025, though it was flagged as spam. I’m not entirely sure why the payment still came through.

Also, I’m unable to cancel the subscription from my side — you’ll need to do this directly in Stripe. To cancel:
  1. Log in to Stripe.
  2. Go to the Customers tab.
  3. Search for the client by email.
  4. Open the subscription details.
  5. Click Cancel subscription.

Could you please check with her if she did in fact submit it on May 28, 2025? If it seems her card may have been compromised, it would be best to kindly suggest she deactivate it for safety.

Really appreciate your help with this!

full_threads.body:
Hi Adrian,

Thank you for bringing this to our attention — I completely understand your concern.

The issue has now been resolved. Upon review, we discovered that the code responsible for cancelling subscriptions wasn’t functioning as expected. We’ve cancelled your subscription manually and updated the code to ensure this doesn’t happen again.

Just to clarify, the $1 charge you noticed is a temporary authorisation used to securely verify and save your card details with Stripe. It is not an ongoing charge.

We sincerely apologise for the confusion and any inconvenience caused, and we truly appreciate your patience while we addressed this.
